This was my first time going to this location, I normally go to Starbucks that’s located at the Brickyard but I was running errands and decided I’d visit this one instead. I go inside to pick up my mobile order and I do understand because of the pandemic their are a few restrictions. I was unable to read that we weren’t allowed to touch the drinks which I understand it was my fault but I was in a bit of a hurry and I did touch a drink (which later turned out to me mine). The guy then proceeded to bark at me “don’t touch the drinks” multiple times. I get caught up, his yelling actually scared me and I apologized for touching the drink. Which he then tells me to stand at the markers, very rudely by the way, they have in place, I did obey though. A few people come in and he doesn’t tell the customers to stand at the markers, which makes no sense, the customers were equally as close as I was before he told me move. He then asks for the mobile order name, which I informed him I came to pick up two orders. I say my name Rocio, which I do consider having a mask makes it impossible to hear but I repeat my name over 10 times. He then pretends to makes some orders and has me wait around 5 minutes before asking for my name again which I do tell him, and tells me to speak up because he can’t hear me. I know for a fact I was practically yelling because I was speaking how I speak at work (I work at a restaurant and the cooks can’t hear me so I have to yell them the orders sometimes). Which at that point I just spelled it out to him, he sees the drink I touched and realized it was mine. He didn’t even apologize for the wait, I was standing there with my drink in front of me unable to touch it for a total of about 7 minutes. By the time I got my drink the ice has melted. And the girl with purple hair even rolled her eyes when I was yelling my name. I understand it can get frustrating but acting rude and rolling your eyes isn’t very professional. The guy then asks for my second order which I tell them the name, and yet again he’s unable to hear me, I just simply spelled it out to him from the start because I wasn’t trying to waste anyones times. He looks around and tells me they are barely making it, I don’t know why honestly, we ordered around the same time. And then proceeded to go to the back, this other guy comes up and asks me for the name of the orders once more and yet he’s able to hear the name perfectly fine. I honestly think you might have to show the workers that their are more diverse names with accents on them. I will definitely not be going here again. It was quite a scary experience, I’ll just stick to my regular Starbucks. Btw even If I did touch a drink that wasn’t mine, would they not want to change it out? I’d personally would have redone it just to make sure it was not contaminated.

I visited this Starbucks location solely to utilize the WiFi to assist me with my homework, and the fact that it sits a few stores down from a FedEx Office so I can print my homework once completed. I arrived to this location prior to 7:00 PM, thinking that it closed at 8:00 PM, but little did I know that it closed at 9:00 PM. As the clock struck 8:00 PM, I noticed that the baristas did not inform anyone that there were closing so I looked them up to find that they closed at 9:00 PM. Realizing that it closed at 9:00 PM, and not 8:00 PM put me at ease and it gave me some wiggle room to finish my homework assignment.  After the relief, I ordered a Teavana tea w/ a blueberry scone, so that I could contribute to this location in some way since I did use their WiFi to assist me with my homework. As I did my homework, I overheard the bubbly barista to customer conversations along with the sound of the espresso machines, which sometimes both can be annoying depending on my mood. I put on one of my favorite songs 'Heads Will Roll' by Yeah Yeah Yeahs to somewhat drown the chatter out and alter my mood in the process.  Seating is actually limited at this location. There is only one solid table and a long-board work station along the window, but other than that, there is nothing else so keep that it mind if you choose to visit during the morning and afternoon hours when it tends to get crowded. As for parking, your only option is either street or neighborhood. There is a tiny parking lot behind this location, but it is for tenants only! And if you park in it, you are liable to get towed by S&S Towing so keep that in mind unless you  do not mind contributing funds to S&S Towing, along with your vehicle, hehe.  My return to this location mirrors this visit unless I get the craving for a mocha latte after printing out homework late evening at the FedEx Office that sits near.  Thomas G
